The paper deals with a game-theoretic approach to incentivizing worker processors in a computing system, which falls under the category of algorithmic game theory (cs.GT). The use of repeated games and strategic decision-making also suggests a connection to distributed computing (cs.DC) and distributed systems (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the use of incentives and penalties, which are common in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and networked systems (cs.NI).
